The earliest known traces of wine are from Georgia (c. 6000 BC),[10][11][12][13][14][15] Iran (Persia) (c. 5000 BC),[16][17] and Sicily (c. 4000 BC).[18] Wine reached the Balkans by 4500 BC and was consumed and celebrated in ancient Greece, Thrace and Rome. Throughout history, wine has been consumed for its intoxicating effects.[19][20][21]
